-- ── egroupware ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$EGroupware is an open-source groupware suite for email, calendaring, contacts, file sharing, and project management, available as free self-hosted software or paid cloud and enterprise editions.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium / Open Source$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (Community Edition); paid cloud plans from EUR 21.90/month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2003, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Small business, privately held$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Kaiserslautern, Germany$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$, $q$German$q$, $q$French$q$, $q$Spanish$q$, $q$Italian$q$, $q$Dutch$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$EGroupware Review 2026: Features, Pricing & Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$EGroupware is an open-source groupware platform for email, calendar, files, and collaboration. Compare Community Edition, cloud, and enterprise pricing for 2026.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$EGroupware is an open-source groupware and collaboration suite that combines email, shared calendars, contact management, task and project tracking, file storage, and team chat into a single self-hostable platform. It is positioned as an open-source alternative to Microsoft 365 and Google Workspace for organizations, particularly in Europe, that want to keep collaboration data under their own control rather than in a large US-based cloud. The software traces its roots to 1996, when the underlying groupware concept was first developed to support a German personnel-training agency's internal workflows. In 2003 the project was forked from the earlier phpGroupWare codebase and relaunched under the GPL as EGroupware, establishing it as an independent open-source project with a growing community of contributors. Commercial stewardship of the project passed through Stylite AG before EGroupware GmbH, based in Kaiserslautern, Germany, took over the business division in September 2016 and has run the project since.

Technically, EGroupware is a PHP-based web application backed by a MySQL, MariaDB, or PostgreSQL database, deployed either on a customer's own servers (on-premises) or through EGroupware's own cloud hosting in German data centers. Its modular architecture bundles core applications including Mail, Calendar, Addressbook, InfoLog (task and CRM-style tracking), Filemanager, Projectmanager, and a helpdesk/ticketing module, and it can be extended with third-party or custom apps. Real-time document editing is handled through an integration with Collabora Online, and video conferencing is supported via bundled Jitsi or BigBlueButton integrations. Mobile users sync calendars, contacts, and tasks with native Apple and Android device calendars and address books using standard CalDAV and CardDAV protocols, and a dedicated mobile app is also available.

EGroupware is distributed under two license tracks. The Community Edition (CE) is released under the GPLv2 and contains the full core functionality with no artificial limitations, making it free to download, self-host, and modify indefinitely. The Enterprise Professional Line (EPL) adds features aimed at larger organizations, such as additional applications, more advanced administration tools, and access to paid vendor support, and is licensed per named or concurrent user on an annual basis. Organizations that do not want to manage their own servers can instead subscribe to EGroupware's hosted cloud plans.

Pricing for the cloud plans starts at eCloud NGO at EUR 21.90 per month for nonprofit organizations and eCloud at EUR 24.90 per month for standard commercial use, both requiring a minimum of two concurrent users, with Collabora document editing and Rocket.Chat team messaging available as metered add-ons. A flat-rate eFlat School plan is available at EUR 1,295 per year for unlimited users, aimed at educational institutions, while the top-tier eFlat plan for larger organizations is quoted on request. For self-hosted deployments, the on-premises EPL Smart package starts at EUR 62.50 per month for a minimum of ten concurrent users, with additional users billed at EUR 4.95 per month each, while the top Universal tier is custom-priced for large-scale or highly customized rollouts. Support for the free Community Edition is available separately at an hourly consulting rate. All published prices exclude VAT.

EGroupware's target users are small and mid-sized businesses, public-sector bodies, schools, and nonprofits, particularly in Germany and the broader European Union, that need a full collaboration suite but prefer open-source software, data sovereignty, or lower long-term licensing costs compared to proprietary alternatives. Its closest competitors include Nextcloud (which focuses more on file sync and sharing with added collaboration apps), Zimbra Collaboration, and the proprietary incumbents Microsoft 365 and Google Workspace. EGroupware differentiates itself by offering a genuinely free, fully-featured GPL edition alongside a clear enterprise upgrade path, German-hosted cloud infrastructure for data-residency-conscious customers, and native groupware features like InfoLog and integrated helpdesk ticketing that go beyond simple file sharing. Notable facts include its two-decade-plus project history, its GPLv2 licensing that predates most modern open-source collaboration suites, and its continued operation as an independently owned German software company rather than a venture-backed startup.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'e78263bf-152d-483f-a33a-9b78428215b6';

