-- ── Elai ──────────────────────────────────────────────
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Elai is an AI video generation platform that turns text and slides into presenter-led videos using AI avatars and voices, aimed primarily at corporate training and e-learning content creation.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Freemium / Subscription$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (1 minute); paid plans from $23/month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2021, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Part of Panopto (acquired late 2024)$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Seattle, Washington, United States (parent company Panopto)$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Elai.io Review 2026: AI Video Generator Pricing & Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Elai.io turns text into AI avatar videos for training and e-learning. See 2026 pricing plans, key features, pros and cons, and how it compares to Synthesia.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Elai is an AI video generation platform that converts written scripts, slides, or documents into presenter-led videos featuring AI avatars and synthetic voices, without requiring cameras, actors, or traditional video production. It was co-founded in 2021 by Vitalii Romanchenko and Alex Uspenskyi, and the flagship Elai Builder product launched in 2022, where it was recognized as the number one Product of the Day on Product Hunt shortly after release. The platform grew quickly by focusing on a specific niche within the broader AI video category: corporate training, onboarding, and e-learning content, rather than trying to serve marketing and social video creators as its primary audience. By the time of its acquisition, Elai had built a customer base of more than 2,000 organizations, including large enterprises such as Fujitsu, Beiersdorf, and Generali. In late 2024, Elai was acquired by Panopto, a video platform company best known for lecture capture and enterprise video management software used widely in higher education and corporate learning and development, positioning Elai's AI avatar generation as a complementary capability inside Panopto's broader video ecosystem.

Technically, Elai works by having users either write or paste a script, or upload an existing document or PowerPoint presentation, which the platform's AI then converts into a video featuring a chosen AI avatar reading the content aloud in a synthesized voice. Users can customize slides with their own branding, images, and templates, and the tool automatically generates avatar lip-sync and gestures matched to the spoken script. A distinguishing feature of Elai's platform is its support for interactive video elements embedded directly in the player: branching paths based on viewer choices, clickable buttons, hotspots, text-based quizzes, and image-based quizzes, which let training teams build assessment and engagement directly into a video rather than bolting it onto a separate LMS quiz. The platform supports 80 or more diverse AI avatars and more than 75 languages with over 450 regional accents, making it well suited for multinational organizations that need to localize training content at scale without re-shooting video.

Elai's pricing is structured around monthly video-minute budgets rather than a flat seat fee. The Free plan provides one minute of video generation with no credit card required, giving new users a genuine hands-on trial of the avatar and language library before committing. The Creator plan costs $29 per month billed monthly, or roughly $23 per month billed annually (about $276 per year), and includes 15 minutes of video generation per month in full HD with access to the complete avatar, voice, and language library. The Team plan, Elai's most popular tier, costs $125 per month billed monthly or about $100 per month billed annually ($1,200 per year), and includes 50 minutes of video per month for three editors and three guest collaborators, along with 4K Ultra HD export, 100 or more premium voices, custom image and font uploads, custom background music, custom templates, workspace collaboration tools, image-based quizzes, and automatic translation; additional minute allotments (100 or 150 minutes per month) are also available at this tier. The Enterprise plan is custom-priced and offers unlimited users and custom minute allocations, three included voice clones, three included selfie avatars, premium avatar access, brand kit tools, single sign-on (SSO), SCORM export for LMS compatibility, direct Panopto integration, SOC 2 compliance, dedicated onboarding and product training, and premium support. Additional a la carte add-ons are available across plans, including a custom Studio Avatar for $500 per year, a personal Selfie Avatar for $199 per year, voice cloning for $200 per year, and extra video minutes at $2 per minute on paid plans.

Elai's target users are corporate learning and development teams, HR and onboarding departments, internal communications teams, and e-learning content creators who need to produce large volumes of instructional video without traditional filming, translation, or voiceover costs. Its most direct competitors are Synthesia, the market leader in AI avatar video generation and the platform Elai is most frequently compared against; HeyGen, known for fast-turnaround marketing and social-style avatar videos; Colossyan, which also targets corporate learning specifically; and D-ID, known for its underlying avatar animation technology. Elai differentiates itself through its deep focus on interactive, quiz-enabled training video and SCORM/LMS export, its acquisition-driven integration with Panopto's enterprise video infrastructure, and pricing that is generally positioned below Synthesia's comparable tiers for teams with moderate monthly video-minute needs. Notable facts include its rapid rise as a Product Hunt-recognized launch, its enterprise customer roster spanning global brands like Fujitsu and Generali, and its 2024 acquisition by Panopto, which folded a five-year-old AI video startup into a much larger, established enterprise video company.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '1e765d41-8506-4bbb-8502-4b6b293c5c29';

